  {
    "client_msg_id": "d8997952-cb43-4850-891c-c805c3ad07e9",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "The aspect I find most appealing is having 'one portal' for all stuff. Currently I log into portal#1 (my laptop) - here I get my local files and apps only. One app (firefox) has me log in to portals 2, 3, 4 (gmail/gdrive, github, <http://futureofocoding.slack.com|futureofocoding.slack.com>) - each one completely siloed away - and has its own set of artifacts. I have various systems in place to sync and various rudimentary import/export mechanisms to move stuff around between these portals, and the nature of computing/programming is very different too.\nOn the web, every app is in fact a new portal to a new siloed world. I hope we have have one world where all artifacts are possible, can interlink etc and we can program here too.",
    "user": "U8A5MS6R1",
    "ts": "1549218810.854800",
